  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How much does it cost to register a trademark in the U.S.?",
  "response": "As of 2023, the cost to register a trademark with the United States Patent and Trademark Office (USPTO) varies depending on several factors, including the type of application and the number of classes of goods or services you are registering. Here are the general costs:\n\n### 1. **TEAS Plus Application:**\n   - **Cost:** $250 per class of goods or services\n   - **Requirements:** Requires more upfront information, including selecting goods/services from the USPTO's pre-approved list and providing an email address for correspondence.\n\n### 2. **TEAS Standard Application:**\n   - **Cost:** $350 per class of goods or services\n   - **Requirements:** More flexible than TEAS Plus but requires less upfront information.\n\n### 3. **TEAS RF (Reduced Fee) Application:**\n   - **Cost:** $275 per class of goods or services\n   - **Requirements:** Offers a reduced fee for applicants who agree to file electronically and communicate with the USPTO via email.\n\n### Additional Costs:\n- **Response to Office Action:** If the USPTO issues an Office Action, responding to it may incur additional costs, particularly if you need to hire an attorney.\n- **Declaration of Use (Section 8):** Between the 5th and 6th year after registration, you must file a Declaration of Use, which costs $225 per class.\n- **Renewal (Section 8/9):** Every 10 years, you must renew your trademark, which costs between $400 and $500 per class, depending on the filing method.\n\n### Professional Fees:\nIf you choose to hire a trademark attorney to assist with the application process, their fees will be in addition to the USPTO filing fees. Attorney fees can vary widely depending on the complexity of the application and the attorney's experience.\n\n### Summary:\n- **TEAS Plus:** $250 per class\n- **TEAS Standard:** $350 per class\n- **TEAS RF:** $275 per class\n\nKeep in mind that these fees are subject to change, and additional costs may arise depending on the specifics of your application. Always check the USPTO website for the most current fee schedule and requirements.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
